    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-conchiglie-and-spinach-pasta-bake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to crisp</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-conchiglie-and-spinach-pasta-bake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>conchiglie</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>conchiglie</strong> for 5-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Tip: It doesn't need to be fully cooked, as it will go in the oven later!</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong>\u00a0conchiglie</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-conchiglie-and-spinach-pasta-bake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chorizo is beginning to crisp, add your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes </strong>and <strong>soft cheese</strong>\u00a0to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-conchiglie-and-spinach-pasta-bake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it<strong> </strong>to the pan with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and mix everything together</p><p>Cook, covered, for 1-2 min or until the spinach has wilted \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy tomato chorizo sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-conchiglie-and-spinach-pasta-bake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-conchiglie-and-spinach-pasta-bake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked conchiglie</strong> to the creamy tomato chorizo sauce and stir it all together until the pasta is fully coated in the sauce</p><p>Season with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Transfer the mixture to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 10 min or until the cheese has melted and the pasta is bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>chorizo, conchiglie & spinach pasta bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chorizo-conchiglie-and-spinach-pasta-bake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve your <strong>chorizo, conchiglie & spinach pasta bake</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
